            "sentences": [
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "The basic idea of unit tests is:", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "Add tests for every method in every object.", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "Check: Does this method do what\nit's supposed to do?", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "For example, you could add a unit test for $bug->add_group.", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "Does it correctly\nupdate the Bug object when a valid group is added?", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "Does it correctly throw an\nerror when you try to add an invalid group?", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "There are various modules in the Test:: namespace on CPAN that help with this\nsort of testing.", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "In order to do this, we need to be able to have a test database that is\nseparate from the real database.", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "What I'm thinking is that we can add SQLite\nsupport to Bugzilla, and then have the tests:", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "1) Create a test database before starting the unit tests.", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "2) Populate that test database based on some variables set in constants\n   in a Bugzilla::Test package (or something like that).", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "There may also be unit testing frameworks for Perl that we could use, although\nI know nothing about that.", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "(The standard testing framework for Perl is\nTest::Harness, of course, and most people use Test::More on top of that, but\nthere might be additional modules or frameworks we can use for writing unit\ntests.)", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }
            ], 
            "name": "Max Kanat-Alexander", 
            "email": "Max Kanat-Alexander"
        }, 
        {
            "date": "2008-01-12 09:58:41", 
            "sentences": [
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "Barring any other unit test framework, I was thinking we would have modules in\nthe Bugzilla::Test namespace named after the standard modules, and we would\nhave functions named after the methods we were going to test.", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "So, for example, to test Bugzilla::Bug::create, we would have a function called\nBugzilla::Test::Bug::create.", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "The Bugzilla::Test modules would live under t/, I was thinking, not under our\nnormal Bugzilla/ directory.", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }
            ], 
            "name": "Max Kanat-Alexander", 
            "email": "Max Kanat-Alexander"
        }, 
        {
