        }, 
        {
            "date": "2008-10-14 08:38:17", 
            "sentences": [
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "(From update of attachment 343048 [details])", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "General comments:", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "Perhaps it might be a good idea to create a Bugzilla::MockObject, a subclass of\nTest::MockObject (or some similar CPAN class) for this.", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "Instead of creating a DB manually and all that, I think that we should just\nhave a separate localconfig.test or something, that checksetup.pl can create\nwith a --test-db argument or something like that.", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "Then we can have a\nUSAGE_MODE_TEST or something as an argument for Bugzilla->usage_mode that will\nswitch Bugzilla->localconfig to reading localconfig.test.", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": ">ok (Bugzilla::Keyword::keyword_count() == 0 , \"No keywords in DB\");", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "You should be using \"is\" instead of \"ok\" here.", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "Or if you really want to force\na numeric comparison, you should be using \"cmp_ok\".", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "(Same comment for all your\ncomparison tests.)", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": ">my $keyword = Bugzilla::Keyword->create(", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": ">    { name => 'foobar', description => 'Keyword foobar' });", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "You should be calling \"isa\" on the return value, to make sure it returned\nsomething.", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": ">$dbh->do(\"INSERT INTO keywords (bug_id, keywordid) VALUES (?", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": ",?)\"", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": ",\n>            undef, 100, 1);", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": ">", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": ">$dbh->do(\"INSERT INTO keywords (bug_id, keywordid) VALUES (?", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": ",?)\"", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": ",\n>            undef, 200, 1);", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "There should be no direct SQL in any of your tests, because that will be hard\nto maintain.", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": ">ok (scalar(@$allkeywords) == 1 && $allkeywords->[0]->{bug_count} == 2,\n>    \"Retrieved all keywords\");", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "You should never be accessing a hash member directly.", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "Instead you should be\ncalling the bug_count method.", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "Also, that should be two separate tests, not one test.", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": ">eval {", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": ">    $keyword2 = Bugzilla::Keyword->create(", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": ">        {name => 'foobar', description => 'Keyword foobar'});", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": ">};", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "Instead of calling an eval, you should use Test::Exception.", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }
            ], 
            "name": "Max Kanat-Alexander", 
            "email": "Max Kanat-Alexander"
        }, 
        {
            "date": "2008-10-14 08:39:43", 
            "sentences": [
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "Also, please don't do work directly on this bug.", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "This is a \"meta bug\" meaning\nthat it tracks work to be done in other bugs.", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "File a new bug specifically for\nthe Keyword tests and make it block this one.", 
